\title{Graphics Processing Cluster (GPC)}

\p{A Graphics Processing Cluster (GPC) is a top-level hardware partition inside an NVIDIA GPU. It's one level up from the [SM](OGCS6) in the chip's hierarchy.}

\p{As of Hopper, [SMs](OGCS6) located in the same GPC are connected via an SM-to-SM network, enabling [DSMEM](OGCS8).}
